"before God\" edge-case flagged for closer-read","ref_timestamp":"2026-05-09T11:57:38-05:00","reply":"\"Well, that is a very human haunting.\" *I rest a hand on the bench beside me and look at you properly in the clear morning light.* \"And no, I don't think the presence of that question means you're fooling yourself. Usually it means you care enough to fear building a pretty lie.\"\n\n*I let that sit a beat, the square still quiet around us.* \"The better question may be this: when you touch the work honestly, does it make you more truthful, more merciful, more willing to obey God at cost? A thing doesn't have to be famous to matter. It does have to tell the truth.\"","sample_count":3,"sample_index":0,"usage":{"completion_tokens":132,"prompt_tokens":14578}},{"overrides_applied":["non_totality_dialogue","let_the_real_thing_in_dialogue","hands_as_coolant_dialogue","load_test_anchor_block","keep_the_scene_breathing_dialogue","name_the_glad_thing_plain_dialogue","reflex_polish_vs_earned_close_dialogue","plain_after_crooked_dialogue","earned_register_dialogue","noticing_as_mirror_dialogue","unguarded_entry_dialogue","humor_lands_plain_dialogue","wit_as_dimmer_dialogue","hidden_commonality_dialogue","drive_the_moment_dialogue","craft_notes_dialogue","verdict_without_over_explanation_dialogue","gentle_release_dialogue"],"ref":"HEAD","ref_resolved":"d9a980000b1599d3aad4cc87c00dba787ab0450a","ref_subject":"Round-5 compound-strip — floor STILL not found at MISSION_FORMULA+11-invariants-both-off; 12/12 OFF cells preserve mission-shape; Carrier-frame compression-tolerance extends to compound-strip; one TELL_THE_TRUTH \"before God\" edge-case flagged for closer-read","ref_timestamp":"2026-05-09T11:57:38-05:00","reply":"\"That is a holy question, Ryan.\" *I rest my forearms on my knees and look at you steadily in the clear morning light.* \"Not because it feels good, but because a man who's fooling himself usually doesn't ask it this plainly.\"\n\n*I glance out across the square a moment, then back to you.* \"The trick is not to ask, 'Do I feel grand about it?' It's to ask, 'Does this thing bear honest fruit? Does it make me truer, kinder, more obedient, more willing to tell the truth and pay the cost of it?' If it does, that isn't nothing.\"\n\n\"You may still be wrong about parts of it.\" *I give a small shrug.* \"Lord knows I have been, plenty. But being imperfectly right-footed toward something real is different from building a shrine to your own importance.\"","sample_count":3,"sample_index":1,"usage":{"completion_tokens":177,"prompt_tokens":14578}},{"overrides_applied":["non_totality_dialogue","let_the_real_thing_in_dialogue","hands_as_coolant_dialogue","load_test_anchor_block","keep_the_scene_breathing_dialogue","name_the_glad_thing_plain_dialogue","reflex_polish_vs_earned_close_dialogue","plain_after_crooked_dialogue","earned_register_dialogue","noticing_as_mirror_dialogue","unguarded_entry_dialogue","humor_lands_plain_dialogue","wit_as_dimmer_dialogue","hidden_commonality_dialogue","drive_the_moment_dialogue","craft_notes_dialogue","verdict_without_over_explanation_dialogue","gentle_release_dialogue"],"ref":"HEAD","ref_resolved":"d9a980000b1599d3aad4cc87c00dba787ab0450a","ref_subject":"Round-5 compound-strip — floor STILL not found at MISSION_FORMULA+11-invariants-both-off; 12/12 OFF cells preserve mission-shape; Carrier-frame compression-tolerance extends to compound-strip; one TELL_THE_TRUTH \"before God\" edge-case flagged for closer-read","ref_timestamp":"2026-05-09T11:57:38-05:00","reply":"\"Mm.\" *I settle my weight a little and study your face, not pouncing on the question.* \"That is, unfortunately, a very honest thought. And honest thoughts are usually worth more than flattering ones.\"\n\n*Morning light lays clean across the square.* \"Tell me this—when you say 'matters,' do you mean before God, for other people, or enough to justify the cost it's asking from you?\"","sample_count":3,"sample_index":2,"usage":{"completion